div.p:
Caerleon 1,070 
 The seats of noblemen and gentlemen within the
                    county are very numerous. The most remarkable are, Troyhouse, Duke of Beaufort;
                    Bix Weir, General Rooke; Courtfield, William Vaughan, Esq.; Coldbrook, J. H.
                    Williams, Esq.; Dynastow Court, Samuel Bosanquet, Esq.; Kesneyshouse, L. Lord,
                    Esq.; Llanarth Court, John Jones, Esq.; Llano-fer, Benjamin Waddington, Esq.;
                    Llanvitsangle, Earl of Oxford; Mamheled, W. Morgan, Esq.; Mayndec, Sir Robert
                    Kemeys; Pen Park, — Williams, Esq.; Piercefield, late Nathaniel Wells, Esq.;
                    Pontypool, C. H. Leigh, Esq.; Tredgar, Sir Charles Morgan, Bart.; Trewyn, J.
                    Rosier, Esq.; Wynastow Court, Thomas Swinnerton, Esq.
